OL,5,CHORSES RESCUE FORT                     
OL,7, Conservationists have recruited three  
OL,8, shire horses to help save an historic  
OL,9, civil war fort overlooking the mouth of
OL,10, the River Dart in Devon.               
OL,12, Gallants Bower, built in 1645 by       
OL,13, Royalists has been attacked by trees   
OL,14, damaging its foundations.              
OL,16, The National Trust called in horses    
OL,17, to clear woodland and undergrowth      
OL,18, because tractors or other machinery    
OL,19, could damage the fragile earthworks.   
